PS, what he says in German is "Rindfleischetikettierungsüberwachungsaufgabenübertragungsgesetz" which literally means "Cattle marking and beef labeling supervision duties delegation law." This was a law of the German state of Mecklenburg-Vorpommern of 1999, repealed in 2013. It dealt with the supervision of the labeling of beef. LOL. The name is famous as an example of the virtually unlimited compounding of nouns that is possible in many Germanic languages.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5lvKwS1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hauntologist2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Vote</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/I7PogS4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GuUIKIB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Tj8PLKp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MLmkmHq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TKmDwzx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/K4faFG5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZHbu3QF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pToWixX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZweQGKX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://twitter.com/RndmStreetMedic/status/1523752777377144834?t=tEiSuQBf9jiZLvv0XD220A&s=19</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/I7PogS4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AllAnusMorissette]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Oof</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JxSrQNu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sLF92oG.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JxSrQNu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GloriososOnibus]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I have been keeping a secret</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zKmH6tA</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PWsy759.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My family is going through a lot individually and I've been very mum about this struggle I've been going through.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/p3oncKw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In vague terms, I've been "high risk" for irregular cell growth and cancer, so I've been dealing with invasive biopsies and screenings for a long time.
But my screening this week came back fully negative for all risk factors.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wCXhsO2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I sound ignorant but I'm trying to live in this joy for a little bit.
Nobody cares, so into the meme void it goes.
Here is my perfectly cat shaped girl.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zKmH6tA</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CakesAndClowns]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I want a nasty little Jewish Princess.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/5HRdVyc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4NOetnC.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sha, la, laa!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5HRdVyc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeirdAlisMySpiritUserName]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I am no longer homeless!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p46Q9f2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/two6vci.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was my bed in the homeless shelter. It was jokingly referred to as the luxury suite because I had two walls between me and anyone else. That level of privacy is indeed a luxury when you are living in a shelter.

Plus I had a chair. For someone who came off the streets, having your own chair is an amazing feeling. Yes, it is a surplus doctor's office chair with all the level of actual comfort that implies, but it was a chair nonetheless.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SXyr8NL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was my locker in all of its empty glory. This was a good shelter where you could actually lock up your belongings and not have to carry them wherever you went.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/flKaSgb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was my lounge area. We could sit here and watch the TV that I'm standing in front of when I took this picture.

Seriously. If you are homeless in north New Jersey, jump through whatever hoops you have to in order to get into Homeless Solutions in Morristown. They are good people and worked hard to get me into a place that I could finally call home.

https://www.hsinj.org</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WPZ0Zhj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is the cafeteria area. Two actual meals a day and a continental breakfast. The meals are cooked and served by volunteers, and run the gamut from edible to OH MY GOD THIS IS GOOD GIVE ME SECONDS! Shepherd's pie night always falls into the latter category. Trust me on that one.

It took me four months to learn about this place. Once I did, I managed to squeeze in here after only two weeks.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/x60urST.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is the bathroom. Pretty boring, but it was important to stay clean in there. Otherwise you had a whole bunch of pissed off homeless people complaining about your stink.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SP55ZQo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was all of my belongings. Two and a half years of homelessness, and I was able to fill up half of that bin with what came out of that locker.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/h7MkOG8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And these are my keys! My actual keys! I haven't had a door I could lock since I left my abusive ex in September of 2019. And I've got to tell you, it was an amazing feeling to just put these on my keyring.

And yes, I purposely hid the key for the front door of the building. I do know that much.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jr9Xdnp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I still can't believe that this is my living room. Corner window, beautiful hardwood floors, a built-in bookshelf for my soon to be massive collection of books. And it is mine.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/scmPZt0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is my tiny kitchen. It is pretty much only for one person to maneuver in, but it is mine. There is no way I could afford this level of luxury without Section 8 benefits, but I'll take it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6WGSsCi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I have an actual bathroom with an actual bath! That first soaking is going to feel so incredibly good.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nFPUy4o.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All of the belongings in my cart are in this pile. The luggage was donated by an anonymous kind soul, and I think the smaller suitcase has already polluted my apartment with glitter. But it's okay, because I have an apartment!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ddX76LV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A cedar closet. Seriously. How did I luck out so much to get a cedar closet?</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CqG1zf2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here is the living room all furnished. And probably as clean as it ever will be again. 

All my furniture was donated to The Warehouse NJ. If you are in northern New Jersey and have some old furniture laying around collecting dust, please consider them for your donations. They are still setting up for the wave of refugees from Ukraine, and could use more stuff to set those folks up.

https://thewarehousenj.org</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2kUv5ET.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And my bedroom. And my bed. MY BED!

The folks from The Warehouse brought the wrong size bedframe and will bring that later on. But that doesn't matter, because I have a bed in a bedroom that is all mine.

I just needed to gush about all the wonderful things that have happened to me. If it dies in usersub, then it dies.

Most Viral edit: Someone below has asked for my Amazon Wish List, so I might as well post it here as well. Thank you to everyone for the well wishes!

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/D3XIANGPRWG7</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/p46Q9f2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[porpoiseoflife]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Advice for the ladies</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bJHqGnk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HugxSvn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link: https://twitter.com/emrazz/status/1522394178499530752</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bJHqGnk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LetsGoBidenFckOffBrandon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Haven?t you tried not doing that thing?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/v14DRbp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xAiKVTj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>(originally posted by @BrazilianThunderPanda on 2021-05-11 08:29:41)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/v14DRbp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThisTimeLastYear]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>They haven't changed</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ums7DTr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4eiulsP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ums7DTr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[angelinesg7]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I'm 40 and just learned how to fully clean my oven.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/3Zyg98J</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gahRn88.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Why did noone ever tell me those doors come off and apart?</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/3Zyg98J</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TheRealSleepIsForChumps]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Be like rosie</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YzHNPhY</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt=""